When i was watching i just forgot everything else ... I was feeling background music in my heart beats...

Talking about the movie !!! before the movie began i was expecting the stupidity and over acting from Varun Dhawan which he has been carrying on in his films since his debut in "Student of the year" but once the movie started i felt that under Shoojit Sircar, Varun almost underwent a complete metamorphosis !!! his acting was great as a carefree 21 year old person who literally had no ambitions and no objectives.. and took everything for granted be it his job, life and even friends..!! The thing noteworthy to observe in this 1 hour 56 min classic was Varun's transition from 21 year old childish guy to a mature 21 year old person once he emotionally attaches himself with Shiuli played by Banita Sandhu ( his junior hotel management trainee) after she meets up with an accident..!! The newbie Banita also gives full justice to her character of Shiuli.. even with few dialogues to her name... her character totally made the presence felt in this film.. You will adore her first, then you will sympathize her and finally you will feel her aura after the movie ends. All in all it's a great film.. shows that even in toughest times all you need is faith and patience .. It also shows that under such tough time you understand who actually are your loving and caring ones and who are just for the name sake..!!

I fell in love with October without liking it so much. The cinematography, background score and the slow and sombre tone of story development made me fall in love with the film. But it didn't really last long as I did come to terms with the fact that the chemistry between the two lead roles hasn't been given as much attention initially. We finish the movie not knowing why Dan acted so impulsively during the first few scenes in the hospital. I also don't think showing him as a successful sous chef in the end was necessary and if anything it diminished the realism that was so carefully carried in the movie. But the beauty of the movie still stays with me.

The movie was bang average in my opinion. Good themes but has probably the worst protagonist of a serious drama I have seen in a long time. He does show some growth, but the comedic moments came off so forced that it made him look like an idiot.
The trailer is also quite misleading, but to be fair, it would have been difficult to make a trailer for such a movie without spoiling the story.

It is not a love story, it is a story about love. The line fits perfectly to the thin script of October, but again thin script not necessarily means a bad film. The way Shoojit Master Sircaar executed such a simple story is what makes the film extraordinary.. The title is best suited while the analogy between the flowers and Shiuli played by Banita is something which shakes your soul. First half is formal introduction of leads working as interns in a 5 star hotel. This is not about one sided love, this is not about intense sensual love, this is about Unusual and unique love. One such movie which shows the unselfish side of love, where there are no conditions, no expectation and no relations. .
Shoojit handles the story very well, the story was thin yet beautiful and hard hitting. The direction often shines bright when some scenes will stir the soul out of you. Juhi chaturvedi's writing was simpler yet it was engaging, the pace won't matter when yofu can take so much from each scene.. Varun dhawan as Dan is relatable, lovable and an extra emotional fool for whom you will feel through out the film. Banita as Shiuli is stands out in her part. Supporting cast was perfect and
 it did gave you a feel of typical Shoojit Sircar's film. The flowers and the shiuli analogy at end was beautiful..
October is not a film, it is an experience. You'll enjoy it if you feel it and you'll enjoy it only by taking a part of it with you.

I have watched serious movies &  liked them in the past. million dollar baby, aashiqi 2 ,sadma, tere naam, baazigar, sharabi,  & many others which have a sad end or the actor dies. but they have a wonderful story or message. we see the characters are grey shades. or there are some circumstances which led the person behave in a particular way.  but this movie October could have been better if put in more thoughts. the actress got very little role & opportunity to act. before we get to discover her character, before we get to know her, she meets an accident. varun dhawan takes care of her. but we don't see what difference did she make in his life, how did her death change his way of looking at life? everything remains the same & movie ends with varun dhawan taking care of her plant, as a remembrance. if I say I got up in the morning, brushed my teeth, went to poop, had breakfast, than lunch, then snacks in evening, & finally ate dinner at night & went to sleep, or probably I died. is this a story? shoojit sarkar is taking his name for granted. maybe he started to feel tht just becoz of his name ppl will flock the theater. If you say in terms of quality i.e. Acting, Screenplay, creativity, theme, story etc Marathi is the best film industry in India though it has less number of viewers because of language and theater availability issues. Marathi produces high quality movies in the lowest budgets in India and has been consistently winning multiple national and international awards.

Nowadays, Golden Lotus is like reserved for Marathi movies. If you take a big budget or rival movie like Sairat then it has 15-16 International Awards already won before coming to theaters. We rarely see such things in Hindi film industry though it has very high budgets.

One of the reasons, why Marathi is doing so good is because, Marathi people are driven by aethics not by family raj like Khans or Kapurs in Hindi, they give importance to qualities of actors while selecting for movie.

Another reason being Marathi has a great culture of theater plays. Usually, it's convention in Marathi that to work in the movie, the person should have done a fabulous job in theater play (as plays don't have retake) .

Rest for Tamil and Telugu, Tamil is the big budget industry like Hindi, while Telugu has somewhat lesser budgets as compared to Tamil. Still, when it comes to movie, we don't find much difference in the kind of films Hindi and Tamil produce. Most of the times, Tamil films are one step ahead of Hindi in terms quality that's what I can say. When it comes Rajinikanth, he brings some new topic and his acting is great ( though some north Indians don't like that but it shouldn't be cared)

Now coming towards Telugu, Telugu is the best industry when it comes to Young Love. Telugu produces very nice love stories, though you will find same storyline in multiple of movies, one boy, one girl and one villain, but still representing the same with different ways each time is very nice in Telugu. Another one theme is Allu Arjun movies, people of just not Andhra or Telangana but from other states too go crazy on his unique style. The song quality in Telugu is also good, they produce a lot of good melody songs. Nowadays Telugu is also experimenting something new like Marathi, and Bahubali was a great example of that and the film became most earning film of 2015 with 650 CR Rs revenue. So, ultimately if Telugu keeps experimenting new, it has big financers also where Marathi lags, then it can literally compete Hollywood

To all those who are saying that Varun Dhawan hasn't done any flop movie till now, please allow me to explain that 

In India, if your movie will be hit or flop is decided by earning to cost and an average movie costs about Rs 5 crore and since population is 125 crores and movie tickets, let's assume that on an average cost Rs 100 then there isn't an stunning possibility that movie won't be a hit. 

Besides, our people are not left with an urge to demand logic or taste or story from movie because of the ongoing shit (movies) for like 70 years.  So they'll watch any movie anyways. 

And movies that do flop, are the ones that are guaranteed to be flop even before release. Like when Himesh Reshamiya builds conflict with Salman (whose fan following is biggest in country) and then leaves singing and acts in movie still people give chance to Tera suroor and Radio but not to Kajra Re. So people have something called bearing capacity but it's too much so movies, in general, can't go flop.

From my understanding to the October trailer;
It says “This is not a love story” meaning they were never in love, but they were just two ordinary people who works in a Hotel. The girl really likes the boy, but she didn’t Know that she loves him until she got sick; then She said his name or asked for him. The soft hearted boy heard that and was surprised and felt for her. He is so into her that he spends most of his time in the hospital. When the girl asked him to leave and go and she will manage everything he said no I’m never gonna leave you. So basically “this is a story about love” means that it’s about the feeling of love and how love happens. This is to my understanding and I meant no disrespect to anyone or the movie.

जिनको ये ट्रेलर समझ में नही आ रहा वो जरूर पढ़े---

Varun और Banita sandhu एक होटल मैंनेजमेंट के स्टूडेंट रहते हैं। वहां पर study कम, काम ज्यादा करना पड़ता है। varun कहता है - सर क्या हम सिर्फ मक्खियां मारने आये हैं।
शुरू में varun को थोड़ा confused and irritated दिखाया गया है, इसकी वज़ह आगे चलके समझ में आती है।
दरसल Banita किसी हादसे के कारण कोमा में चली जाती हैं और लास्ट टाइम हास्पिटल में  सिर्फ इतना पूँछ पाती हैं कि where is Dan (varun)?
Varun को जब ये बात पता चलता है तो वो confused हो जाता है , वो सोचने लगता है कि उसने सिर्फ उसी के बारे में क्यूँ पूँछा? क्या वो मुझसे प्यार करती थी?
इस बारे में जाननने के लिये वह Banita की friend से पूँछता है, कि क्या कभी college में उसने तुमसे मेरे बारे में पूँछा था? 
जवाब में वो कहती है कि- मुझे नही लगता कि उसे तुममे कोई interest था या वो तुम्हें पसन्द करती थी ।
Varun काफी परेशान हो जाता है । वह कहता है तब उसने मेरे ही बारे में क्यों पूँछा? 
फिर हास्पिटल का एक सीन आता है, Banita के यूरीन ज्यादा करनें पर varun नर्स से पूँछता है आज ये यूरीन ज्यादा क्यूँ कर रही है, क्या तुमने इसे पानी ज्यादा दिया है? इस पर नर्स  गुस्से से कहती है, क्या तुम्हारे पास कोई काम नही है क्या?
क्योंकि अब Varun , Banita को लेकर कुछ ज्यादा ही protective हो लगता है। उसकी friend उसे समझाती है कि वो Banita के लिये protective न होकर अपने काम पर ध्यान दे। 
उसके इस अंदाज से साफ ज़ाहिर होता है कि varun को भी Banita से प्यार हो गया है।
वह सब कुछ छोड़ छाड़ कर हास्पिटल चला जाता है । Banita के घर वाले भी उसके ठीक होने की उम्मीद छोड़ देते हैं, उसके घरवाले कहते हैं कि अब तो वो हम लोगों को पहचान भी नहीं रही । और Varun कहता है कहता है कि वो नही पहचानती तो क्या हुआ हम तो उसे पहचानतें हैं। अब यहां पर बिल्कुल साफ हो जाता है कि varun भी उससे प्यार करने लगा हैं।
फिर Banita हास्पिटल से डिस्चार्ज हो जाती हैं , वो सोती-जागती तो है पर न तो कुछ बोलती है न ही कुछ खाती हैं। यानी अब भी वह कोमा से बाहर नही आती है।
Varun धवन एक अच्छे माहौल के उद्देश्य से उसे हिल-स्टेसन ले जाता है। वह जी जान से पूरी कोशिश करता है कि Banita ठीक हो जाये लेकिन ऐसा नही होता ।
आखिरकार Banita की Death हो जाती है और Varun को एक बड़ा सदमा लगता है। इसके बाद varun अपने घर आ जाता है, उसकी माँ उससे कहती है कि इतने दिनों के बाद तुझे मेरी याद आयी? 
Varun कहता कि  माँ अब तुम्हे छोड़कर कही नही जाउँगा। 
अंत मे Varun अपने आप से बाते करने लगता है,  उसे लगता हैं कि Banita उसके पास बैठी है और वो उससे बाते कर रहा है। परंतु Varun खुद से बाते कर रहा होता है।
और मूवी समाप्त हो जाती है।

मूवी का नाम October इसलिये है क्योंकि ये सारी घटनाये October में होती हैं।
